        "text": "### What you're looking for\n\nThe standard reduction potential:\n\n$$\\text{Cu}^{2+}(aq) + 2e^- \\rightarrow \\text{Cu}^0(s) \\quad E^\\circ = +0.337 \\text{ V vs. SHE}$$\n\nThis value (+0.337 V at 25 °C, standard hydrogen electrode reference) comes from **electrochemical thermodynamic databases**, such as:\n\n| Source | Value (E°, V vs. SHE) |\n|---|---|\n| NIST WebBook / CODATA | **+0.3419 V** |\n| CRC Handbook of Chemistry | **+0.337 V** |\n| Atkins' Physical Chemistry | **+0.34 V** |",
